  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and manage construction projects from initiation to completion, delivering results within budget, schedule, and quality standards</li><li>Coordinate effectively with clients, consultants, subcontractors, and site teams to ensure seamless project execution and stakeholder alignment</li><li>Develop, monitor, and adjust project schedules to mitigate risks and implement corrective actions proactively</li><li>Ensure strict compliance with local building regulations, safety requirements, and obtain necessary authority approvals</li><li>Review project drawings to identify discrepancies and provide practical, site-based solutions to maintain project integrity</li><li>Conduct thorough site inspections to verify workmanship quality meets required standards and specifications</li><li>Manage project costs by controlling variations and optimizing resource allocation for maximum efficiency</li><li>Prepare detailed progress reports, documentation, and updates for management and clients to maintain transparency</li><li>Lead problem-solving initiatives to resolve site challenges and unforeseen issues, ensuring project continuity</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree or Diploma in Civil Engineering, Architecture, Construction Management, or a related field</li><li>Minimum 8 years of experience managing construction projects, with preference for A&A and landed house projects</li><li>Proficiency in MS Project and MS Office for project scheduling and documentation</li><li>Strong leadership skills demonstrated by managing cross-functional teams and driving project success</li><li>Proven problem-solving skills applied to site management and project challenges</li><li>In-depth knowledge of construction processes, local building regulations, contract administration, and safety standards</li><li>Ability to coordinate multiple subcontractors and trades efficiently to meet project objectives</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience specifically in A&A and landed house construction projects</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Offer Salary: 5k-6.5k</li></ul>",
